{# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   NOTE: This file is intentionally NOT a Jinja2 template.

   The EBA report XLSX is built programmatically via openpyxl in `report.py`
   (function `render_xlsx`). Jinja2 cannot reliably produce styled, multi-sheet
   Excel binaries — the EBA submission portal validates cell formats, so we
   construct the workbook from `models.EbaReport` rather than rendering a
   template.

   This file documents the layout that `render_xlsx` is contractually required
   to produce. If you change the schema below, update `render_xlsx` to match.

   Layout (one sheet per Annex):
     * Cover     : header metadata (PSP LEI, name, country, quarter, period, submission ID)
     * A         : Annex A  — payment volumes & values
                   columns: instrument, channel, tx_count, tx_value_eur
     * B         : Annex B  — fraud breakdown
                   columns: instrument, channel, fraud_type, fraud_count,
                            fraud_value_eur, loss_value_eur
     * C         : Annex C  — SCA exemptions
                   columns: instrument, sca_exemption, tx_count, tx_value_eur,
                            fraud_count, fraud_value_eur, fraud_rate_bps
     * D         : Annex D  — loss allocation
                   columns: instrument, loss_bearer, counterparty_geo,
                            fraud_count, loss_value_eur
     * Totals    : period totals dictionary

   Style:
     * Header cells: fill #1F4E78, bold white 11pt, centred.
     * Title row: bold 14pt #1F4E78, merged A1:H1.
     * Frozen pane: A4 (header row visible while scrolling).
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- #}
